```{r setup, include=FALSE}
knitr::opts_chunk$set(echo = TRUE)
```

```{r}
startups <- read.csv("startup data.csv")

str(startups)
summary(startups)

startups$success <- ifelse(startups$status == "acquired",1,0)

names(startups)[names(startups) == "Unnamed..6"] <- "location"

```

```{r}
logit1 <- glm(success ~ . -state_code -zip_code -state_code -id -object_id -location -name -city -closed_at -founded_at -first_funding_at -last_funding_at -is_othercategory -category_code -state_code.1 -is_otherstate -status -Unnamed..0 -labels -is_top500, data = startups, family="binomial")
summary(logit1)

```

```{r}
logit2 <- glm(success ~ age_last_milestone_year + relationships + is_otherstate + is_gamesvideo + avg_participants + has_VC, data = startups, family="binomial")
summary(logit2)
```
